HEADWORD: Untidy
<hw>Un*ti"dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Unseasonable; untimely.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Untidy</xex> tales.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Piers
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not tidy or neat; slovenly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*ti"di*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*ti"di*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

